@startuml
!pragma layout smetana
title 05. Supervisor Agent LangGraph Orchestration

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ActivityDiamondFontSize 12

start

:Build running context;
:Call planner for routing + review decision;
if (planner says review required?) then (yes)
  :Freeze planner result for review;
  :Create immutable reviewed execution snapshot;
  :create WAITING_REVIEW task;
  :open review ticket;
  stop
endif

:Mark RUNNING task via persistence facade;
:Load reviewed execution snapshot + history/checkpoint/swarm via ExecutionStateLoader -> ReadFacade;
:Build typed graph input via SupervisorGraphInputBuilder;
:Invoke CompiledGraph;

:SELECT node;
if (routing plan exists?) then (yes)
  :INVOKE node;
  :record invocation batch to SwarmState;
  :HANDOFF_EVALUATE node;
  if (accepted handoff exists?) then (yes)
    :HANDOFF_APPLY node;
  else (no)
    :keep original routing queue;
  endif
  :MERGE node;
  if (more plans?) then (yes)
    :loop back to SELECT;
  endif
else (no)
endif

:COMPOSE node entered;
:<back:FFE7A8>Compose outside graph;
note right
<size:10>CallLLM</size>
end note
:Emit graph/routing summary via SummaryEmitter;
:Collect final result channels via ExecutionResultCollector (sync/resume only);
:Persist task/review/checkpoint/swarm via ConsistencyCoordinator + PersistenceService;

stop

note right
Current graph contract
- nodes: select, invoke, handoff_evaluate, handoff_apply, merge, compose
- no HITL wait node inside graph
- planner decides `review_required` and builds routing queue before graph invoke
- planner is outside graph; graph never calls planner directly
- select -> (invoke | compose)
- invoke batch size is bounded by execution.maxConcurrency
- max iteration guard exists
- handoff is feature-flagged and policy-validated
- graph input assembly is outside graph
- summary/progress publish is outside graph
- missing/invalid `review_required` is fail-closed and never downgrades to auto-pass
- review approve resumes reviewed snapshot with frozen routing plan, not raw request re-run
- direct execution and approved resume both enter graph at ROUTING_SELECTED
- progress/reasoning remain stream-only and are excluded from persisted result payload
end note
@enduml
